        <num>CC 1256</num>
        <heading>1256.  Immovables collated in kind; reimbursement for improvements</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1256.  Immovables collated in kind; reimbursement for improvements.
The donee who collates in kind an immovable, which has been given to him, must be reimbursed by his coheirs for the expenses which have improved the estate, in proportion to the increase of value which it has received thereby.</p>
        </content>
